description:
Recently sold: $470,000. Stunning TH in highly sought-after Boulder Ridge community. Privacy abounds this 4BD, 3BA, open concept 3600+ sq ft home with prime location on pond. Unlike any other TH in Boulder Ridge. Single-level living on main - boasts large open floor plan, vaulted entrance and solid hickory h/w floors. Kitchen has granite counters and large center-island with SS appliances, cabinet pullouts, and beautiful dining room adjacent with gorgeous views of pond and magnificent willow trees. Walkout to large 2-tier deck overlooking pond, fountain and gazebo.  Living room is open to the kitchen and has floor-to-ceiling brick fireplace and wall of windows overlooking large deck and pond.  MBR with boxed ceiling, bay window, and large walk-in closet and private master bath with frame-less shower door and jetted tub. 2nd upper bedroom has custom-built Techline Murphy bed.
Lower level features new flooring and an expansive family room with floor-to-ceiling stone fireplace, wet bar, two large bedrooms with walk-in closets, 3/4 bath and fully finished workroom/storage area.
Nearly new HVAC, water heater, and Cedar Shake roof. Solid 6 panel doors, large front paver patio, finished garage floor with drop-down stairs and additional storage in attic. Updated recessed lighting and paint throughout. Picturesque views of the pond and grounds from every room in the house. Private screened-in gazebo for bonus outdoor living.  Mature trees, private, setting and one of largest units in the Boulder Ridge community.  Almost $90k in upgrades.

description: Recently sold: $406,000. This landmark Plymouth home is a spacious, light-filled retreat, surrounded by woods and a 17 acre park. A completely custom mid-century modern inspired home with open-concept living, soaring ceilings, wide-plank wood floors, oversized windows, and two wood burning fireplaces. The home features 3 large bedrooms with walk-in closets on the same level, including a master bedroom with en suite bathroom, upstairs laundry, and an oversized three car garage. The walkout basement with wet bar is perfect for entertaining and includes a spacious 4th bedroom that can also function as a quiet office space. Enjoy the secluded natural setting on the back screen porch without the long country driving distance. The home is surrounded by tennis courts, playground, skating rink and more and a few minutes drive from ample grocery, dining, and retail. Less than 20 minutes to downtown Minneapolis. Unparalleled character and amenities, this home is beyond compare.

Recently sold: $262,000. This corner unit is hard to beat! Totaling approximately 1,900 square feet, it features 3 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, and an open main level floor plan in which the kitchen, dining area, and living room are not divided by walls. Add in the 9 foot tall ceilings and the extra corner unit windows to get a main floor that feels extremely inviting and open! But if you need more privacy just pull down the custom-fit blinds that are installed on all the main floor windows and most of the upper floor windows. Never shovel snow again! The unit includes an underground heated garage stall for two cars and all the shoveling of the front walkways is included in the rent. The garage also has considerable storage space with 4 massive built-in sturdy wooden shelves. The unit is primely situated within walking distance to French Park and near a local Target with the Arbor Lakes Shopping area only 4 miles away. The front door opens to a shaded porch running the length of the front of the unit and is surrounded by well-manicured landscaping. 

One or two year leases available with a move in date as early as August 1st, 2013. Monthly rent of $1,750 includes water, garbage, garage heating, and all snow removal/lawn care (renter is responsible for electric, gas, and optional internet/cable). No smoking and no pets.

Email or call 952-412-7016 with any questions or to schedule a showing.

List of Amenities/Featured Rooms: 

Kitchen
-Tons of counter space and cupboards 
-All appliances included (refrigerator, oven, microwave, dishwasher, garbage disposal)
-Moen brand faucets throughout entire unit
-Hardwood floors throughout kitchen, dining area, bathroom, and front entrance
-Under-cabinet lighting and dimmer light switches in main kitchen and dining area

Living Room
-Gas fireplace
-Custom dimmable track lighting in living room with pendant lights over bar stool eating area

Master Bedroom/Bathroom
-Walk-in closet
-Ceiling fan
-Large double vanity
-Laundry located on upper level (washer and dryer included)

Recently sold: $420,000. Contact Danny Dietl, danny@brixtwincities.com or 612-306-6676 for more information. Open house Sunday May 19th 1-3pm.
Immaculately maintained two-story home with extensive updates on quiet street and situated on a nearly 1/3rd acre lot. Main level features attached two car garage, laundry, 1/2 bath, formal living room, formal dining room, kitchen (appliances 2015) with sliding glass door to deck and cozy family room with fireplace. Upper level has a full bath and three bedrooms including a large master with walk-in closet and private 3/4 master bath. Walkout lower level offers a wet bar, 3/4 bath, two bedrooms, living room with built-ins and gas fireplace and office space.

Recently sold: $485,000. Exceptional home on a quiet cul de sac, perfect for entertaining! Walkout lower level leads to incredible pool with adjacent pergola covered patio, and tiered deck overlooking the privately fenced backyard. Interior features vaulted ceilings with a very functional flow for everyday living. Spacious master suite with private en suite and walk-in closet. Main level living room and family room with gas fireplace. Lower level amusement room also has wonderful entertaining space with beautiful gas fireplace and full wet-bar. description:
Recently sold: $435,000. This spectacular 3,500 sq feet mansion feels twice bigger than the typical homes of comparable size because of its unique and very thoughtful layout. 

It has 2,500 sq ft ABOVE GROUND! This is true hidden treasure of Plymouth.

It features:  4 bedrooms, 5 bathrooms, huge living room, modern kitchen with skylight window, dining room and sunroom - all with vaulted ceilings, family room with the very efficient and useful wooden fireplace, and spectacular Jacuzzi room having three 6x6 windows, shower, hot tub and the best in the town cedar sauna, in addition to heated tile floor and walkout. The lower level spacious den can be used as a second family room.  The laundry room is big and has second refrigerator with freezer, and a window .  There is huge maintenance free deck to which you can get from three (!!!) entree points, from all levels: from family room/office, from sunroom and from Jacuzzi room. There is huge crawl space that is always dry and can serve as a storage and a shelter. The house has 20 rooms in total. In addition: it features beautiful cherry laminate floors all over the family room and living spaces, and 2.5 cars attached garage. 

Location: quiet cul-de-sac (only 4 houses), complete privacy, wilderness and a pond in the back of 0.4 acres of land, and yet the proximity to all major highways (494, 169, Northwest Blvd, and 55). Walking distance to the French Park, and 5 minutes drive to the main shopping centers - east, west, south and north of the location. Crime free neighborhood and very friendly neighbors, and much more.... 

Priced for quick sale.

Twin Cities Northwest Suburbs: The Twin Cities Northwest metro area is made up of several suburbs including Plymouth, Maple Grove, Coon Rapids, New Hope, Crystal, Golden Valley, Brooklyn Park, Brooklyn Center and Robbinsdale. If you are looking for good schools with competitive sports programs, some of the best are in this region including Wayzata (which is where over 50% of Plymouth residents attend), and Maple Grove. The Northwest region is also a convenient rental choice, as it is near to several major are employers including General Mills, Boston Scientific, TCF Financial, and Honeywell. The northwest Twin Cities also has quick and easy access to I494, and I394, highways 169 and 100 and various MTC public transit systems. I394 is also convenient for downtown Minneapolis commuters. Preferred malls and shops west of the Twin Cities include Ridgedale Mall located in Minnetonka, the new Westend Shops located in St. Louis Park and the shops at Arbor Lakes located in Maple Grove. The hot spots for rentals have been geared towards upper bracket townhome and condo rentals in the Plymouth and Maple Grove areas. Properties having a minimum of two bathrooms and a two car garage have been most popular. Upgraded kitchens, including stainless steel appliances and wood floors, have been featured selling points for renters.
